The paper deals with a generative model for visual dialogue, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and its intersection with computer science. The second most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), which deals with CV techniques. The paper also involves machine learning (ML) techniques, which are covered in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper proposes novel evaluation measures and metrics, which are covered in cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
